BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 4: Nutrition for Thyroid Health) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (Essential Nutrients for Thyroid) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (- Iodine: Needed to make thyroid hormone \(seaweed, fish, iodized salt\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (- Selenium: Converts T4 to T3 and reduces antibodies \(2-3 Brazil nuts daily\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (- Zinc: Required for T3 production \(pumpkin seeds, beef, oysters\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 614.2 Td (- Iron: Necessary for thyroid enzyme function \(red meat, lentils\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 600.2 Td (- Vitamin D: Immune modulation \(sunlight, fatty fish, supplement\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 586.2 Td (- B12: Energy and nerve function \(animal products, supplement\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 572.2 Td (- Magnesium: Supports conversion and reduces inflammation) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 542.4 Td (Foods to Emphasize) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 524.4 Td (- Wild-caught fish \(salmon, cod, sardines\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.4 Td (- Brazil nuts \(2-3 daily for selenium\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 496.4 Td (- Seaweed in moderation \(iodine\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 482.4 Td (- Grass-fed meat and organ meats) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 468.4 Td (- Eggs \(contain iodine, selenium, B12\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 454.4 Td (- Colorful vegetables and fruits) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 440.4 Td (- Fermented foods \(gut-immune connection\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 426.4 Td (- Bone broth \(gut healing\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 396.6 Td (Foods to Consider Limiting) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 374.6 Td (For Hashimoto's specifically) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 358.6 Td (- Gluten: Strong association with Hashimoto's - trial elimination recommended) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 344.6 Td (- Dairy: Can be inflammatory for some) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 330.6 Td (- Soy: May interfere with thyroid medication absorption) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 316.6 Td (- Raw cruciferous vegetables in LARGE amounts \(cook them instead\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 302.6 Td (- Excess sugar and processed foods \(inflammation\)) Tj ET
