100 0 obj
<< /Length 2645 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Frequently Asked Questions) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Q: Why does my doctor say my labs are 'normal' but I still feel terrible?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (Standard lab ranges are very wide. You can be 'within normal' but far from optimal.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (Advocate for a full panel and ask about functional/optimal ranges. Consider a functional) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 632.2 Td (medicine practitioner.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 604.4 Td (Q: Can Hashimoto's be reversed?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (The autoimmune process can be slowed or put into remission \(lowered antibodies, improved) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.4 Td (function\). Gluten elimination, selenium, and gut healing show the most promise.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 546.6 Td (Q: Should I avoid all goitrogens \(cruciferous vegetables\)?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.6 Td (No. Cooking reduces goitrogenic activity by 80%. Only raw, massive quantities cause) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 516.6 Td (issues. Cooked broccoli, cauliflower, etc. are healthy choices.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 488.8 Td (Q: Can stress affect my thyroid?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 472.8 Td (Absolutely. Stress increases reverse T3 \(blocks active T3\), suppresses TSH, and in) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 458.8 Td (Hashimoto's can trigger autoimmune flares. Stress management is essential.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 431.0 Td (Q: How long does thyroid medication take to work?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 415.0 Td (You may notice some improvement in 2-4 weeks, but full effects take 6-8 weeks. Labs should) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 401.0 Td (be rechecked 6-8 weeks after any dose change.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 373.2 Td (Q: Is natural desiccated thyroid \(NDT\) better than levothyroxine?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 357.2 Td (Some patients do better on NDT \(contains both T4 and T3\), while others do well on) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 343.2 Td (levothyroxine alone. Work with your doctor to find what works for you.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 315.4 Td (Q: Can I exercise with hypothyroidism?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 299.4 Td (Yes, but honor your energy levels. Start gentle, progress slowly. Overexercise can worsen) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 285.4 Td (fatigue. Walking, yoga, and moderate strength training are excellent choices.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 257.6 Td (Q: Does gluten-free really help Hashimoto's?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 241.6 Td (Multiple studies show gluten-free diets reduce thyroid antibodies in Hashimoto's patients.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 227.6 Td (The molecular structure of gluten resembles thyroid tissue \(molecular mimicry\). Trial 3-6) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 213.6 Td (months.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
